# Secret manifest — single source of truth for which secrets exist, where they
# live in 1Password, and which keychain store they sync to.
#
# `env/setup.sh` reads each row, pulls the value from the given 1Password
# account via `op read --account`, and caches it in the macOS keychain under
# service "<store>", account "<store>-<name>". Consumers look the keychain up at
# load time (no plaintext on disk): the nono `ai` profile reads the "nono" store
# (its env_credentials resolve "nono-<name>" accounts at sandbox startup), and
# the *.mise.toml templates read the "mise" store. Items are added with `-A` so
# reads never trigger a keychain password prompt.
#
# Columns (whitespace-separated; only <op://reference> may contain spaces):
#   <store>            "nono" if the secret is exposed to the AI sandbox via the
#                      nono profile, else "mise". Used for BOTH the keychain
#                      service (-s <store>) and the account prefix (<store>-<name>).
#   <name>             secret name; cached as keychain account "<store>-<name>"
#   <op://reference>   1Password secret reference (op read ...)
#   <account>          1Password account: sign-in address, email, or account ID
#
# NOTE: fill in the real op:// references and accounts for your items below.
#
